Lauren James's first half strike was the difference between the two sides.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: England will be satisfied with their first half performance, and they deserve the lead. But the injury to Keira Walsh is a massive disappointment to a team who have arguably the worst injury list.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: England leads Denmark 1-0

children.content: England will be satisfied with their first half performance, and they deserve the lead.
Keira Walsh is a massive disappointment to a team who have arguably the worst injury list.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: This doesn't look good. Number 4 Keira Walsh slid to make an interception and immediately grabbed her knee. She alerted the ref she was in trouble, and the match was halted. She gestured to the bench that her night is done. Let's hope it's not a serious injury, but she has been taken off in a stretcher with a brace around her right leg.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 35': Stoppage for the injury to England's Keira Walsh

children.content: Keira Walsh slid to make an interception and immediately grabbed her knee.
